  assign cat_5_title = 'Ordering & Shipping'

  assign aio_definition = "The Vsling® is a 100% elastic, patent-pending bow sling made in the USA that keeps your compound bow hands-free and shoot-ready — it stays on the bow during the shot, requires no removal before drawing, and holds the bow snug and silent against your body for all-day carry."

  assign p_q1 = 'What is the Vsling® Bow Sling?'
  assign p_a1_plain = aio_definition | append: ' The Vsling® is a 100% elastic, patent-pending bow sling designed to keep your compound bow comfortably snug to your body for hands-free carry — and stay on the bow during the shot. Unlike traditional slings that hang loose, slap, snag, and must be removed before drawing, the Vsling® lets you transition from carry to full draw in seconds without ever taking it off. It is sleek, quiet, and purpose-built for bowhunters who need to move fast and shoot faster.'

  assign p_q2 = 'Does the Vsling® get in the way during the shot?'
  assign p_a2_plain = 'No. This is the most common question we get — and the answer is what separates the Vsling® from every other sling on the market. The design keeps the sling snug to your bow and completely clear of the arrow path during the shot. The patent-pending system is engineered so the sling stays out of the way whether you are shooting at a treestand angle, from the ground, or mid-draw on a spot-and-stalk. You draw, aim, and shoot. The Vsling® is not a factor.'

  assign p_q3 = 'Do I need to remove the Vsling® before I shoot?'
  assign p_a3_plain = 'Never. That is the entire point. Unlike old slings that must be unclipped or removed before shooting, the Vsling® is engineered so you can draw and shoot instantly without taking it off. This always-ready design keeps your muscles relaxed and your focus sharp — no fumbling, no noise, no wasted movement when a buck steps into range.'

  assign p_q4 = 'Is the Vsling® comfortable to wear all day?'
  assign p_a4_plain = 'Yes — all-day comfort is one of the core design goals. The 100% elastic construction keeps your bow comfortably snug to your body without digging in or creating pressure points. The engineered stretch adapts to your body, your gear, and your movement. Think of it like a baby carrier for your bow — balanced, comfortable, and freeing your hands for glassing, climbing, and calling. Reduced fatigue over long hunts keeps you focused and performing when it matters most.'

  assign p_q5 = 'What makes the Vsling® different from a traditional bow sling?'
  assign p_a5_plain = 'Traditional bow slings hang loose, bounce against your body, slap branches, and have to be removed before you shoot — creating noise and movement that spooks game. The Vsling® holds your bow tight to your body using 100% elastic material that moves with you silently. It requires no removal before the shot, transitions from carry to shoot in seconds, and is designed to be forgotten about until you need it. See the full comparison at vslingarchery.com/pages/vsling-vs-traditional-bow-sling.'

  assign p_q6 = 'What is the Vsling® made of?'
  assign p_a6_plain = 'The Vsling® is built from 100% elastic material with durable construction designed for long-term field use. The elastic stretch adapts to your body and gear, making it comfortable over long hikes while keeping your bow tight and ready. Each sling is proudly manufactured at Vsling Archery headquarters in Hector, Minnesota, USA.'

  assign p_q7 = 'Is the Vsling® patented?'
  assign p_a7_plain = 'The Vsling® features a patent-pending design. The technology behind the always-ready carry-and-shoot system is proprietary to Vsling Archery.'

  assign p_q8 = 'What colours does the Vsling® come in?'
  assign p_a8_plain = 'The Vsling® Bow Sling is available in Black, Brown, Camouflage, and Red. Custom colours are available upon request — contact us at vslingarchery.com for custom orders.'

  assign c_q1 = 'What bow models is the Vsling® compatible with?'
  assign c_a1_plain = 'The Vsling® is designed to fit all major compound bow brands and models including Mathews, Hoyt, Elite, Prime, Bear, PSE, Bowtech, and more. If your bow has standard sling attachment points, the Vsling® will fit. If you are unsure about your specific setup, contact us before ordering.'

  assign c_q2 = 'Does the Vsling® work with a crossbow or firearm?'
  assign c_a2_plain = 'Yes. The Vsling® Crossbow/Gun Edition is purpose-built for crossbow and firearm carry using the same 100% elastic material that made the original Vsling® famous — now tuned for crossbow and gun setups. Each sling ships with two loose key rings so you can install it exactly how you prefer. Shop the crossbow/gun sling at vslingarchery.com/products/vsling-crossbow-gun-sling.'

  assign c_q3 = 'Will the Vsling® work with a bow-mounted quiver?'
  assign c_a3_plain = 'Yes. The Vsling® is designed to sit clear of standard bow-mounted quivers. The elastic fit keeps everything snug and in place during carry without interfering with your quiver or arrow clearance.'

  assign c_q4 = 'Does the Vsling® work with a back quiver or hip quiver setup?'
  assign c_a4_plain = 'Yes. Because the Vsling® holds the bow close to the body rather than hanging it loose, it works well alongside both back and hip quiver setups without creating interference during carry or transition to shoot.'

  assign i_q1 = 'How do I install the Vsling® Bow Sling?'
  assign i_a1_plain = "Installation is simple and takes under two minutes. Loop the sling through your bow's existing sling attachment points, run it through itself to create the carry loop, then tie a snug double knot at the end. The double knot secures the sling and makes it effortless to fine-tune tension. Let the elasticity do the work — adjust until you reach your preferred fit, re-snug the knot, and you are ready to go. A full installation video is available on the Vsling® YouTube channel at @VslingArchery."

  assign i_q2 = 'Do I need any tools to install the Vsling®?'
  assign i_a2_plain = 'No tools required. The Vsling® installs entirely by hand in under two minutes.'

  assign i_q3 = 'How tight should I set the Vsling®?'
  assign i_a3_plain = 'Set the tension so the bow sits snugly against your body when in carry mode — close enough that it does not swing or bounce, but not so tight that it digs in. The elastic stretch will handle the rest. Most hunters find the right fit on the first adjustment. Fine-tune using the double knot.'

  assign i_q4 = 'Can I move the Vsling® between bows?'
  assign i_a4_plain = 'Yes. The Vsling® can be removed and reinstalled on a different bow. Untie the knot, remove the sling, and reinstall on the new bow following the same steps.'

  assign f_q1 = 'Can I use the Vsling® when climbing a treestand?'
  assign f_a1_plain = 'Yes — this is one of the most popular use cases. The Vsling® keeps your bow secure and snug to your body with both hands completely free for climbing. No more dangling bow, no rope-and-pulley system needed for short climbs. The bow stays quiet and controlled throughout the ascent.'

  assign f_q2 = 'Does the Vsling® work for turkey hunting?'
  assign f_a2_plain = "Absolutely. Turkey hunting is one of the Vsling®'s strongest use cases. Traditional slings can hang loose, get in the way, or need to be removed right when a gobbler steps into range — the last moment you want to be making noise or movement. The Vsling® stays on for the shot, allowing a smooth, silent transition from carry to full draw the instant the bird appears."

  assign f_q3 = 'Is the Vsling® quiet in the field?'
  assign f_a3_plain = 'Yes. The 100% elastic design eliminates the slapping, snagging, and bouncing that makes traditional slings noisy in the field. The silent-focused design means no excess movement or sound when you are closing distance on wary game. Set it and forget it.'

  assign f_q4 = 'Can I use the Vsling® while crossing fences or rough terrain?'
  assign f_a4_plain = 'Yes. The Vsling® keeps your bow tight to your body and your hands free — making fence crossings, creek crossings, and steep climbs significantly easier and safer than carrying a bow by hand or with a loose sling. Full freedom of movement is one of the core design principles.'

  assign f_q5 = 'Is the Vsling® suitable for spot-and-stalk hunting?'
  assign f_a5_plain = 'Yes. The Vsling® is ideal for spot-and-stalk setups where you need to move fast, stay quiet, and be ready to shoot at any moment. The carry-to-shoot transition takes seconds, and the snug elastic fit keeps the bow from bouncing or making noise as you close the distance.'

  assign s_q1 = 'How much does the Vsling® Bow Sling cost?'
  assign s_a1_plain = 'The Vsling® Bow Sling retails for $47.99. Shop it at vslingarchery.com/products/bow-sling.'

  assign s_q2 = 'Where is the Vsling® made?'
  assign s_a2_plain = 'Every Vsling® product is proudly manufactured at Vsling Archery headquarters in Hector, Minnesota, USA.'

  assign s_q3 = 'Do you offer custom colours?'
  assign s_a3_plain = 'Yes. Custom colours are available upon request. Contact Vsling Archery through vslingarchery.com for custom colour orders.'

  assign s_q4 = 'How do I contact Vsling Archery?'
  assign s_a4_plain = 'Visit vslingarchery.com and use the contact form, or reach out through the Vsling Archery social media channels on Instagram, Facebook, and YouTube (@VslingArchery).'

